1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with interference control in cellular networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a load-spillage power control method, which involves optimizing the allocation of power across subbands. This optimization problem can be viewed as an information theory problem. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses rate distribution in the macro network, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel interference control method that involves subband scheduling and interference cancelation, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The paper does not directly relate to this sub-category, but it is possible that the proposed interference control method could have societal implications, such as improving the quality of cellular network services.
